examples:

exp1.py -p instances/ -t 100
or
exp1.py -p instances -t 100
Solve all files in the directory instances (which is in the root directory of the script)

exp1.py -p ../instances -t 100
Solve all files in the directory instances (in the parent of root directory)

exp1.py -p ../ -t 100 -l chosen.csv
Solve all files in the chosen.csv list with path (the ../ indicates that the directory for searching the files is the parent directory)

exp1.py -t 100 -l cho.csv
Solve all files in the cho.csv list with path (-p argument is not needed since we want the current directory to be searched in)

exp1.py -p instances/ -t 100 -r
Solve all files in instances directory recursively